
⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Question 65/120 – Top 3 Employees Per Department

🎤 Interview Question

You are given an employee DataFrame.

Write PySpark code to display the Top 3 highest-paid employees from each department.


---

📊 Input Dataset

department	employee	salary

IT	John	100000
IT	Alice	90000
IT	Bob	80000
IT	Sam	70000
HR	David	60000
HR	Tom	55000
HR	Mike	50000
HR	James	45000



---

✅ Expected Output

department	employee	salary

IT	John	100000
IT	Alice	90000
IT	Bob	80000
HR	David	60000
HR	Tom	55000
HR	Mike	50000



---

✅ Recommended Solution

from pyspark.sql.window import Window
from pyspark.sql.functions import row_number, col

window_spec = (
    Window.partitionBy("department")
          .orderBy(col("salary").desc())
)

result = (
    df.withColumn("rn", row_number().over(window_spec))
      .filter(col("rn") <= 3)
      .drop("rn")
)

result.show()


---

🎤 Most Asked Interview Questions

Q1. Why use row_number() instead of rank()?

Answer

row_number() guarantees exactly 3 rows per department.


---

Q2. What if two employees have the same salary?

Answer

row_number() still returns exactly three rows.

If the business requires handling ties, use dense_rank().


---

Q3. Is this question frequently asked?

Answer

Yes. It's one of the most common PySpark and SQL interview questions.


